meanings.definition: To have eaten more than someone else.
meanings.sent1: She outeaten her brother at the dinner table.
meanings.sent2: The competitive eater outeaten all his opponents in the hot dog contest.
meanings.sent3: The squirrel outeaten the birds at the feeder, leaving them hungry.
meanings.sent4: Her appetite was like a bottomless pit, always ready to outeaten others.
meanings.sent5: The image of her outeating everyone at the buffet stuck in my mind.

meanings.definition: To have consumed more food than is necessary or healthy.
meanings.sent1: He outeaten so much cake that he felt sick afterwards.
meanings.sent2: The children outeaten all the snacks before dinner was even served.
meanings.sent3: The cat outeaten the dog's portion and then napped contentedly.
meanings.sent4: The overflowing plate seemed to challenge her to outeaten it all.
meanings.sent5: The sight of him outeating himself every day was concerning.
